President Barack Obama issued a statement on Armenian Remembrance Day, acknowledging the atrocities that occurred in 1915 when 1.5 million Armenians were massacred or marched to their death in the final days of the Ottoman Empire. He emphasized the importance of a full and just acknowledgment of these facts and the need to learn from these terrible events. President Obama also recognized the efforts of Turks who saved Armenians in 1915 and praised the ongoing dialogue between Turks and Armenians regarding this painful history. He highlighted the remarkable spirit of the Armenian people and their contributions to various communities around the world over the past ninety-five years. The President concluded by expressing admiration for their resilience and hope for the future.